[Event "Baker Bridge - Strong 2C Bids"]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "1"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "None"]
[Deal "S:AK.KQJT4.AJT.KJ9 Q852.A7.Q74.T764 J943.96.9863.A82 T76.8532.K52.Q53"]
[Declarer "N"]
[Contract "3NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
2C pass 2D pass 2H pass 2NT pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 1, chOption: N, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:0, nBasis: 0, nRot: 0, useStandardVul: true"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/strong_2c"]
[Student "S"]
{You dealt this hand.  

With 23 points you open 2\C. Partner responds 2\D.  

You bid your 5-card \H suit. Partner says 2NT.  

Partner's 2NT shows scattered values and fewer than 3 \Hs. He has 3 or more points or he would have bid the Double Negative. So you say 3NT.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "2"]
[Dealer "W"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "W:AK8.KQT.KQJ2.AT4 9652.843.A6.9652 JT7.A96.T95.KQJ3 Q43.J752.8743.87"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "6NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "W"]
2C pass 2NT pass 3NT pass 6NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/strong_2c"]
[Student "S"]
{You have 11 points and partner opens 2\C. Wow! You answer 2NT and he bids 3NT. What is your next bid? 

Hmmm, 22-24 balanced, plus 11 balanced equals 33-35 balanced. It makes you think a jump to 6NT would work out great. Just do it.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "S:AQT64.AQ85.Q7.AK .KJT.AT542.Q8643 9875.64.863.J752 KJ32.9732.KJ9.T9"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "3S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
2C pass 2D pass 2S pass 3C pass 3H pass 3S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/strong_2c"]
[Student "S"]
{With just 1 Jack you bid a Negative 2\D. Partner now bids 2\S. What is your bid? 

Partner's bid of a suit is absolutely forcing, no matter how you feel about it. But now is the time you tell him you have fewer than 3 points by using the Second Negative. You bid 3\C. Partner now says 3\H.  

No, you still may not pass. First, because partner's bid of a new suit is forcing. Second, because even if you were not forced you prefer his first suit. So you bid 3\S and he passes.}

