2C pass 2D pass 3C pass 3D pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: W, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:3, nBasis: 0, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/strong_2c"]
[Student "S"]
{With a true Yarborough you qualify to respond a Negative 2\D. Partner now bids 3\C. What is your bid? 

You now inform partner of your disaster hand by using the Second Negative. Since his suit is \Cs the Second Negative is 3\D. Partner now says 3NT.  

You definitely pass. Good thing he has 9 cold tricks in his hand!}

